__________('android',)__________


Positive Reviews:

---"Pros:-Good hardware (dual-core CPU, two cameras, HDMI output, 8 GB of internal memory, microSD slot)-Good looking interface-Plenty of space to install appsCons:-LG's stock Android becomes slow if you install many apps-Official ICS update is even slower and has no HDMI support-No notification LEDs (but you can use the backlight buttons to emulate them)-In-ear headphones (I don't like them)Conclusion: I bought this phone because I consider myself an advanced user and I rooted it to use a custom Android ROM." **** 'slow'
---'If you want to became familiar with Android and do want to make your hands dirty in rooting and custom roms - GO FOR IT.' **** 'familiar'

Negative Reviews:

---'I have to recommend a 2GB phone as a minimum for Android, especially with the new versions forcing more and more into the onboard memory and off of your SD card, which really makes no sense to me.' **** 'minimum'
---'If you want to became familiar with Android and do want to make your hands dirty in rooting and custom roms - GO FOR IT.' **** 'want'


